hopobject.body: Where do you come from? intel pharma arez black review The galactic bulge is located at a distance of around 27,000 light-years from our point of view. It consists of dense dust clouds and gases, which makes it hard to accumulate precise information. Hence, the first group from the MPE (Max Planck Institute for Extraterrestrial Physics) located in Garching, Germany, used the VVV near-infrared survey from the VISTA telescope. Examining these dust clouds with lights having longer wavelength such as the infrared radiation aided the astronomers in getting a good view through the thick dust clouds and gases.
